&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;ReconnectOnSessionLoss&lt;/code&gt;: When &lt;code&gt;true&lt;/code&gt;, the driver transparently re-handshakes after a server restart and retries the query. Defaults to &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt; because any server-side session state (transactions, &lt;code&gt;SET&lt;/code&gt;, temp tables) is silently dropped on reconnect.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
